cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks, specifically salient object detection using deep convolutional neural networks. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a novel method for learning uncertain convolutional features, which involves the use of dropout and ensemble methods, which are common techniques in machine learning and deep learning. Therefore, it is also likely to belong to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper proposes an effective hybrid upsampling method to reduce checkerboard artifacts, which is a technique used in image processing and computer graphics, making it likely to belong to the cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category as well.
